import React from "react"; const projects = [ { id: 1, name: "Website Redesign", status: "In Progress", deadline: "2026-03-01", icon: "web", color: "bg-blue-100 text-blue-700" }, { id: 2, name: "App UI", status: "Completed", deadline: "2026-02-10", icon: "phone_android", color: "bg-green-100 text-green-700" }, { id: 3, name: "Logo Design", status: "In Review", deadline: "2026-02-20", icon: "brush", color: "bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700" }, { id: 4, name: "SEO Optimization", status: "In Progress", deadline: "2026-03-15", icon: "trending_up", color: "bg-purple-100 text-yellow-700" }, { id: 5, name: "Brand Identity", status: "Completed", deadline: "2026-01-30", icon: "palette", color: "bg-pink-100 text-pink-700" }, { id: 6, name: "Client Portal", status: "In Review", deadline: "2026-02-25", icon: "account_circle", color: "bg-gray-100 text-gray-700" }, ]; export default function Projects() { return (
folder_open Projects
{projects.map((p) => (
{p.icon}
{p.name}
{p.status} calendar_today {p.deadline}
))}
); }
